survey_response.review_text:
Dr. Mani Ramesh did the total knee replacement surgery for my mom in sep 2007. We are going for yearly routine check-up with him and very happy with the surgery, follow-up appointments.

Doctor is very good in explaining and making the patient's understand about their health issue and treatment plans as well. 

Dr. Mani Ramesh helped us in resolving various medical queries for my family members many times and referred us to cardiologist care for my Dad etc., 

I would strongly recommend him for my friends and families

Thanks a lot Doctor.

At  the  outset  I  wish  to  convey  my  special  thanks  for  all  in  the  clinic
for  their  an  encouraging  welcome  and  advices  given.  As  regards  the
consultation  and  inter-action  with  the  Doctor,  it    gave  me  an on the
spot  relief  to  a  great  extent.  Further  the  investigations  recommended
and  explanation  given over  it  upon  receipt  of  results  are  highly  commendable.  THANKS  ONCE  AGAIN  FOR  THE  EXCELLENT  SERVICES
RECEIVED.  with  warm  regards
RENUKA  GOPALAKRISHNAN  &  VR  GOPALAKRISHNAN.
Great doctor listen slowly and explain the root cause of issue and suggest the best feasible practical solution

Dr Mani Ramesh empathised with our family when we went to him for knee replacement of my aged mother. She was most comfortable with him , the way he connected with us and explained to all of us patiently regarding the procedure . He would take pains to explain and brief us post surgery and ensured my mother was taken care of well in the hospital. My mothers mobility really took a turn for the better post the surgery. Best wishes to him

Doctor was too caring and keep on checking about the status of the patient every now and then,he was patient to listen to all our silly doubts and took a very good care of tha patient and also comforted the patient's dear ones with his positive attitude!!

Dr Mani Ramesh is friendly Dr to start with . He Explains the whole structure of the body how  the pain starts and what are best exercises and how to follow daily Routine for pain management. The medication  prescribed by Dr Ramesh very helpful  I am able to  move on with my daily chores and move on.. i strongly recommend DrRamesh for any joint issues. One of the Best Dr in orthofield  i will strongly say yes

I got my finger chopped in a blender and it was a Sunday. Rushed to the hospital and there was no doctor available except a duty doctor who organised to clean and inject me with pain killers. Since my bone also got cut (almost amputation stage) Dr. Mani Ramesh came to the hospital at 12:30 in the night (SUNDAY) to see my condition and explained me thoroughly about the injury patiently at that time and fixed a surgery the next day. He also looped in a Plastic Surgeon and entered the OT with no hope of getting my finger back. But, Dr. Mani Ramesh saved my finger and I am completely satisfied with the treatment and we are associated with Prashanth hospital since 2012 and until now, we go there for anything and everything. Hats off to you Sir.

It was really good. Dr was helpful and explained the situation to me. He administered Curtzone injection . The swelling and the pain subsided. He also gave me information on shoulder exercise.
I am pleased to inform that I am not completely free of any pain.

I would recommend him to all my friends and relatives.

I feel luck to visit this doctor... I hv gone for second opinion when my first doctor told that a biopsy is required by surgery. But Dr Mani Ramesh advised to go for CT guided biopsy which is 4 times lesser cost than surgery and done all the required tests and Now I am fine n recovered completely. I thank Dr Mani Ramesh for his experienced guidance.
He was straight to the point in the consultation and post test scan, findings and treatment prescription/advice.

Thanks to the doctor
